article.headline: Longwood 113, Columbia Union 84
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Antwan Carter had career-highs of 33 points and 20 rebounds to lead Longwood in a 113-84 win over Washington Adventist on Wednesday. Aaron Mitchell added 21 points and 10 rebounds and Martiz Washington had a career-high 23 points for the Lancers. The Lancers (12-19) had season-highs in points and field-goal percentage with (62.3 percent, 43 of 69) in their last game of the season. Longwood outscored the Division II Shock 64-34 in the paint and outrebounded them 49-33, leading to 17 second-chance points. The Lancers, who won their fourth straight, were 6 of 19 from 3-point range, giving them a school record 85 this season. Washington-Adventist was 8 of 11 from 3-point range in the first half and trailed 53-51 at the break. The Shock then went 0 for 6 from long-range in the second half in their fifth straight loss. Jamie Newton led the Shock (9-16) with 24 points.
